Help spread the word - Gustine ISD will start at 9:00 in the morning. UPDATE:
Buses will start at 8:00 am - about 2 hours later than usual. No breakfast will be served.

There are many spots in our area that water has crossed the road. The weather forecast is for the rain to continue throughout the night. Waiting a little later allows us to let the sun come up where it is easier to see what we are driving into on the roads.

Please check Facebook throughout the evening. Any changed to the schedule will be posted to the Facebook page.

post_text:
The Gustine Athletic Booster Club is having a raffle for 4 Texas Ranger tickets and a parking pass. The game is on September 22nd. (The tickets and parking pass have been donated by a community member!) All Gustine JH and HS Athletes have tickets to sell. Price is 1 ticket for $10 or 3 tickets for $20. We will draw the winning ticket at the High School Football Game Half Time on September 14th.

The plan is to use the money to purchase new scoreboards for Tiger Stadium and for Tiger Gym. We have been told by the vendor that they are no longer making parts for our scoreboards. So, we are crossing our fingers that everything keeps working through this season and we can replace them before next school year.

Thank you for your help and support!!

post_text:
I know that word travels fast around here, so many of you have heard that Jack Graves accepted a position in Wildorado. I hate losing him, but I know this move provides a lot of things that are good for his family. I wish The Graves family well as they make this move.

So, I have been searching for a new AD this week. I am happy to announce we have an new AD!! I think this name will be very familiar to many of you - Rodie Johnston has accepted the position. His wife Bonnie will also be joining us as the 4th grade teacher! I am so excited that this has fallen into place!

Rodie will be on board as quickly as he can, but you know the headaches that can come with moving! Rodie and I will be working together through this transition time. We know that August is quickly approaching and we want to make sure our Tigers and Lady Tigers are ready to go!

Welcome Home Rodie and Bonnie!

post_text: Shout out to yesterdays cross country medalists at the Priddy meet in Melody Oaks. Starting off with Jr high boys, they placed second as a team just 2 points behind Priddy!
